  "prompt": "What song plays over the end credits to the 2002 movie Bark?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there isn't widely available information about a 2002 movie titled **\"Bark.\"** It's possible that the film is a lesser-known, independent, or direct-to-video release, which might explain the limited details about its soundtrack.\n\nHere are a few steps you can take to find out which song plays during the end credits:\n\n1. **Check the End Credits:** Often, the songs featured in the credits are listed there, including the song title and artist.\n\n2. **Visit IMDb:** The [Internet Movie Database (IMDb)](https://www.imdb.com/) is a comprehensive resource for movie details. Search for the movie \"Bark\" and navigate to the \"Soundtrack\" or \"Music\" sections to see if the end credit song is listed.\n\n3. **Look for Official Soundtracks:** Sometimes, movies release official soundtracks separately. Searching for a \"Bark (2002) soundtrack\" online might yield results.\n\n4. **Fan Forums and Communities:** Websites like [Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/) or dedicated movie fan forums may have discussions where other viewers have identified the song.\n\n5. **Contact the Production Company:** If available, reaching out to the production company or the filmmakers through social media or official contact channels might provide you with the information you seek.\n\nIf you have access to the movie, watching the end credits closely or using a music identification app like **Shazam** while the credits are playing can also help identify the song.\n\nIf you have any more details about the movie, such as notable actors, plot points, or the production company, feel free to share them, and I might be able to assist you further!",
